ot]], A.D.C. to Lord Hill * Captain Edward Keane, [[7th Queen's Own Hussars|7th Hussars]], A.D.C. to Sir Hussey Vivian * Captain C.A. FitzRoy, [[Royal Horse Guards]] * Captain T. Wildman, 7th Hussars, A.D.C. to Lord Uxbridge (wounded{{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}}) * Captain [[Sir James Fraser, 3rd Baronet|James Fraser]], 7th Hussars (wounded,{{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}} afterwards Sir James Frasier, Baronet) * Captain William Verner, 7th Hussars (wounded{{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}}) * Captain Elphinstone, 7th Hussars (taken prisoner, 17 June) * Captain H. Webster, [[9th Light Dragoons]] * Captain H. Somerset,[[18th Hussars]], A.D.C. to General Lord Edward Somerset * Captain [[Charles Yorke (British Army officer)|Yorke]], 52nd Foot, A.D.C. to Gen. Adam (afterwards Sir Charles Yorke, not present) * Captain Hon. George Gore, [[85th Regiment of Foot (Bucks Volunteers)|85th Foot]], A.D.C. to Sir James Kempt * Captain Pakenham, Royal Artillery * Captain Henry Dumaresq<!--(1792-1838)--><!-- Not to be linked to the Australian cricketer with the same name-->, 9th Foot, A.D.C. to Gen. Sir John Byng (was wounded in the chest by a musket ball, delivering a despatch to Wellington. died 1836){{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}}{{sfn|Urban|1838|p=443}}{{sfn|Gray|1966}} * Captain F. Dawkins, 1st Foot Guards, A.D.C. * Captain Disbrowe, 1st Foot Guards, A.D.C. to General Sir G. Cook. * Captain George Bowles, [[Coldstream Guards]] (afterwards General Sir George Bowles, Lieutenant of the Tower) * Captain R.B. Hesketh, 3rd Foot Guards (wounded{{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}}) * Captain J. Gurwood, 10the Hussars (wounded{{sfn|''Royal Armouries''|2015}}, afterwards Colonel Gurwood) * Captain C. Allix, 1st Foot Guards * Captain Hon. Francis Russell, A.D.C. * Lieutenant F. Brooke, [[1st Dragoon Guards]] (killed at Waterloo<ref name="Killed at Waterloo"/>) * Cornet W. Huntley, 1st Dragoon Guards * Mr. Lionel Hervey (in Diplomacy) * Mr. Leigh * Captain A. Shakespear, 10th Hussars * Mr. 