{{Infobox language |name=Tɔli |nativename=''Tɔli-gbe'' |states=[[Benin]] |region= |speakers=? |date= |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Volta–Niger languages|Volta–Niger]] |fam4=[[Gbe languages|Gbe]] |fam5=[[Phla–Pherá languages|Phla–Pherá]] |iso3=none |glotto=toli1243 |glottorefname=Toli }}
'''Tɔli''' (Toli) is a [[Gbe language]] of [[Benin]]. ''Ethnologue'' counts it and Alada as dialects of [[Gun language|Gun]], but Capo (1988) considers it one of the [[Phla–Pherá languages]].
